	lect:lecture_id"14_X1022";
	sylb:summary ""Co-Creation (in other words, "inclusiveness" and/or "active engagement") process is becoming a key concept in design practices in the 21th century. Also we can find important shifts in various field of design, that should be mentioned as "from Product Design to Experience Design".

In this class, three professional designers will give you very actual and practical experiences of new design paradigm.

(1) Experience and Engagement Design in "Food Design" (by Haruna Nakayama)

Ms.Nakayama is running a food design studio named "ferment (http://www.ferment.or.jp/english)", and cultivating new directions, especially focusing on local ingredients and materials.

(2) Experience and Engagement Design in "Furniture Design" (by Emu Masuyama)

Mr.Masuyama has been working in London for many years, by running his own wood-workshop named "MESA (http://mesa-studio.com/)". He also pays attentions on local materials- like wood, timbers and soil.

(3) Experience and Engagement Design in "Museum Design" (Mr. Edward Schlossberg) A pioneer in this field, a designer based on New York, will give you special lecture and workshops. http://www.esidesign.com/

";
